# Node Version With nvm

When frontend commands fail or may fail because of the active Node.js version, use `nvm` to switch Node first.

Preferred command:

```bash
nvm use 20
```

In this workspace, `nvm use 20` may switch to Node `v20.16.0` on the user's machine. After switching, rerun the intended command such as `pnpm install`, `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm build`, or `pnpm dev`.

If a package declares a stricter engine range than the selected Node version, report the mismatch clearly instead of silently changing dependency or engine settings.
